ited as members on the management body.</FONT><FORM method=post action="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.processVote?topicID=90.topic"><table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width="55%"><tbody><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="1"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Yes</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="2"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>No</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="3"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Restrict them to 6 members or less</FONT></td></tr></tbody></table><P><input type=submit value="Vote"><a HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showMessage?topicID=90.topic&pollResults=on><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Show results</FONT></A> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaethielholyblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aethiel Holyblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/1/01 11:37:36 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/siraethiel/aethiel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Alliances be allowed on CoG Planes Raids? </span><hr size=1> I know this is a poll, but I feel the need to comment on this.<br>
<br>
I personally feel that KCoG dragons and planes raids SHOULD be restricted to those smaller guilds who do NOT belong to alliances. Guilds who belong to alliances, such as mine (Haven of Light/AoVB), will always have the opprotunities to be on rotations for dragons, planes, etc. <br>
<br>
After all, isn't the purpose of KCoG to give smaller guilds the opprotunity to experience these types of raids who otherwise might NEVER get the chance?<br>
<br>
Guilds who belong to alliances generally do participate in rotations for dragons, planes, etc. By letting allied guilds participate in KCoG, I feel and think we take spots from those smaller guilds who can not normally participate on these types of events. <br>
<br>
Please bear in mind this is only MY personal opinion and does NOT reflect on the views of my guild or alliance. I think its safe to say that we have enjoyed the opprotunity to be part of KCoG and are thankful that you have included us your events. I do, however, feel its time for some of us to be a bit more considerate to other smaller guilds. For some people and guilds, KCoG is the ONLY chance for them to experience these events.<br>
<br>
Bearing this in mind, I will in all likelyhood not be attending any KCoG events in the future. Please do not misunderstand me. It is not because of anything that has transpired within KCoG, but rather its because I feel its selfish for me to take a spot from someone else who may not ever have the same opprotunities as me. With that being said, I truly wish all of you the best of luck in KCoG. Haemish keep up the great work!<br>
<br>
Respectfully yours,<br>
<br>
Aethiel Holyblade<br>
Level 49 Paladin of Life<br>
Haven of Light <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/2/01 1:13:01 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Alliances be allowed on CoG Planes Raids? </span><hr size=1> Actually Aethiel, I hope you attend events in the future. ALL of the CoG events are for all on the server. The ONLY events that are restricted are dragon raids, and THOSE are only restricted because of KGC restrictions on who can make up the majority of the raid team on those raids. The planes are NOT currently restricted in this way because KGC doesn't require it. <br>
