<br>
Currently this is the way the CoG works:<br>
<br>
Planes raids<br>
-------------<br>
Ex. 1: Valoran member (a guild that does Planes Raids all on their own, without any other guilds, i.e. not in an alliance) should not sign up for planes raids sponsored by the Council of Guilds<br>
Ex. 2: Sign of One member (a guild that currently does planes raids, but they do it as part of an alliance with the Silent Watch, I believe) CAN and SHOULD sign up for a planes raid sponsored by the Council of Guilds<br>
Ex. 3: Mist Walkers member (a guild that does not currently do planes raids either by itself or in an alliance) CAN and SHOULD sign up for planes raids sponsored by the Council of Guilds<br>
<br>
Dragon Raids<br>
------------<br>
Ex. 1 Valoran member (a guild that is in the dragon rotation by itself) should not sign up for dragon raids sponsored by the Council of Guilds<br>
Ex. 2 Sign of One member (a guild that is in the dragon rotation in an alliance with Silent Watch) should not sign up for dragon raids sponsored by the Council of Guilds<br>
Ex. 3 Mist Walkers member (a guild that is not currently in the dragon rotation either by itself or in an alliance) CAN and SHOULD sign up for Council of Guilds dragon raids<br>
<br>
ALL OTHER Council of Guilds Events<br>
----------------------------------<br>
Unless specified by the organizer, ALL other CoG events are open to ANY of the above examples<br>
<br>
Now what the question above is asking is this:<br>
<br>
In the planes raids examples above, should the Sign of One member (and I'm just using them as an example) sign up for the Planes raids, since his guild can already do the planes, albeit in an alliance? <br>
<br>
The Current Karana Guild Central guidelines (which is the body that keeps the schedules and rotations for planes, dragons and gods) say that if you are in the dragon or god rotation, you shouldn't have a lot of (or even more than 2 or 3) members at someone else's dragon or god raid, because that's giving you an unfair amount of chances at something we've all agreed to share. There is no such restriction on the planes (except that guilds doing the planes by themselves shouldn't be on other people's or alliances planes raids). <br>
<br>
Please keep in mind, the Council of Guilds DOES so much MORE than just planes and dragon raids. They just happen to be what most people seem to fixate on, but it's really just a small portion of what we do.<br>
<br>
