<br>
- Any Guild, or major alliance that frequently attend plane raids are not allowed to go on CoG raids.<br>
<br>
Now, if one person from another alliance, or major guild signs up, I usually look the other way.  As long as the numbers are not extremely, causing me to turn away CoG people I don't care.<br>
<br>
Also, sometime I recruit people from my management staff from other major guilds.  Originally I was thinking of having my plane raids being sponsored by all the other major guilds, and sort of make it Server wide interaction.  However, that never really worked out.  But I still reserve the right up to 12 people of my choosing to help out.  I have only been using like 3 to 4 slots.  And if I bring them along, I have them do some sort of management task.<br>
<br>
Then, there's a few guilds that do not go to planes frequently because all their members except a few have all plane armor.  Again, there's a fine line here, but the whole purpose of this raid is to give the people the chance to go to the planes that couldn't get a chance (primarily because they are in a small guild).<br>
<br>
Afterall, if we want to be technical, I can't go on CoG raids myself, as the The Watchmen are part of the CoK alliance.  They go to the planes just about every week, and are on rotation for the big targets.<br>
<br>
So it is an interesting and valid question.<br>
<br>
