 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/4/01 2:48:54 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Alliances be allowed on CoG Planes Raids? </span><hr size=1> I wish it were that simple, but we are talking about a number of different alliances, all of which have different policies as such. It hasn't really come up before, at least not that I know of. <br>
<br>
How about it? Any of the alliances that are doing planes on their own have some representatives that would like to address this? <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaethielholyblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aethiel Holyblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/4/01 3:16:30 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/siraethiel/aethiel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Alliances be allowed on CoG Planes Raids? </span><hr size=1> Hello all. Well since my posted response, I have had the time to talk to many others and have read many repsonses on this subject. In retrospect, I guess I was a bit hasty in saying I would or should not participate in future KCoG events. My concern was with myself and possibly my guild taking up many spots from other people and guilds. In actuality, there isnt a huge chunk from my guild that usually do participate. Its usually just a couple, if that. So based on what I have read and what has been said, I appologize to you all for my hasty remarks and I hope I didnt offend anyone. If you guys will have me, I'll glady participate with you guys when I can <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Aethiel Holyblade<br>
Level 49 Paladin of Life<br>
Haven of Light <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uchameleosmanaflare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chameleos Manaflare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/4/01 7:46:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://216.10.106.28/chameleos?flezbwidth=80&flezbheight=150 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Alliances be allowed on CoG Planes Raids? </span><hr size=1> I tell you from experience with various alliances and solo guilds, albeit not all, that loot is restricted to their members only unless they all have them. And even then I saw people getting a backup set of armor before letting a guest get something in some cases.  I heard some cases where guilds allowed guests (especially if they are close friends of members) allowed to roll on things no one cared even if they lacked.<br>
<br>
Also may I have an explanation as to why members from guilds who book one plane solo every week are treated differently from a 2 guilds alliance who book one plane every week?  If you are to allow folks, even in a limited number, who are already doing their plane raid in a given week you need to clarify this I think.<br>
 <p>--<br>
<b>Chameleos Manaflare</b><br>
Enchanter 56th, Karana<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/4/01 11:19:44 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Alliances be allowed on CoG Planes Raids? </span><hr size=1> The main purpose I had in posing this question is asking if there are people who are missing out on these raids because of other people who already have a chance to go on planes raids with their own guilds, albeit in an alliance. Since one of the stated purpose is to allow those who aren't able to get to the planes with their guild to be able to experience a plane raid, I would hate to know that there are folks who are being denied this privilege by those who already have this privilege in another form. <br>
<br>
However, looking for every person's guild affiliation and then checking it against the number of alliance out there is a BIG organizational hassle. I would only attempt to restrict it in this if I felt that there were those missing out. <br>
<br>
Haemish MacLennan<br>
Clan Chieftan<br>
The Silver Daggers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/5/01 1:44:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Alliances be allowed on CoG Planes Raids? </span><hr size=1> I was told by a couple Friends of Mine in Bigger guilds that i could come with them to their Planes raids but there were some catches to this.<br>
<br>
1. I would have to do at least 3 raids with them before i got a chance at any loot.<br>
<br>
2. after the 3 Raids I would be allowed to Roll on an Item that i was told i was aloud to roll for (so i would get to roll on Rare gems and Trinkets/Words).<br>
<br>
3. I would not get to Roll on Armor, I would only get armor if no one else needed it.<br>
<br>
I have been told this by friends of mine in a couple different guilds that i have gone along with to either  Planes or even Raids to places such as Dragon Necropolis, where once again i was not alowed to roll on anything.  But i did get the Cobalt scar tooth while going there.<br>
<br>
As to being able to join them on these Raids, it wasnt as simple as a Sign up. I had to leave a post on their Site begging (which I am not good at) to go and if the Guild Leader thought that they could use me i would be alowed to go and only then if they had the space for another person.<br>
<br>
If we have to go through that to go with them, why should they go with us? They have their own space in the rotation and as to timing, I have stayed up till 9 the next morning a couple times to go on raids with my guild leader who plays at the oriental times. Those raids started at 2 in the morning for me. If you want to go on a raid you find a way to do it. The purpose of the CoG raids I'm gathering is so that us smaller guilds who aren't in major planes capable alliances can actually go. I believe VERY strongly that since we cant do 2 raids a week why should they be allowed to? Just because they didn't sign up to go on their own alliance's raid they still had the chance to. Its not like we dont already have waiting lists with CoG as it is.<br>
<br>
Anyway I've ranted long enough.<br>
<br>
Lagdalen Tarcho &lt;Fellowship of Faydark&gt;<br>
lvl 50 Mage Officer <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A> at: 2/5/01 1:49:36 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplangstrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>P Langstrump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/5/01 3:59:12 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://samlaren.se-swed.net/lindgren/pippistor.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Alliances be allowed on CoG Planes Raids? </span><hr size=1> This is just my personal opinion, but I would prefer not to see the CoG do as the guilds/alliances do with lottoing items only among their own and making up special rules for &quot;guests&quot; (heck, everyone here is a &quot;guest&quot;)...for me, that would be stooping down to the common level and falling prey to the &quot;we need to protect our guild/alliance, and everyone else is not as important&quot; mentality. Similarly, I've always thought of CoG as a place where individuals were seen and respected as individuals rather than belonging to a specific guild. <br>
<br>
CoG is not an alliance, and as such, anyone who is willing to volunteer their goodwill and join the fun has an equal say in the events - well, ok, the person organizing has a bit more of a say <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   but who says that you can't organize your own thing for the CoG?<br>
<br>
Verant has set some basic intrinsic game rules, and there are a few additional ones set up by the CoG, but as you may notice, there are only a few limiting ones.  All these rules are publicly and openly discussed here, and if anyone else wants to try out new approaches or systems, here is the forum to suggest and do it ... I've done a couple of atypical rulings and raids on my own, and it's always fun to swim a bit against the stream <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
... just always keep in mind that open and upfront communication is the most critical part of any of these &quot;experiments&quot;<br>
<br>
oh yes, I am making a guess that people who clearly obsess over items won't enjoy CoG events at all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
cheers. pip<br>
